def solve(tuple, k):
    sorted_tuple = sorted(tuple)
    max_elements = sorted_tuple[-k:]
    min_elements = sorted_tuple[:k]
    return max_elements, min_elements

def solve(tup, k):
    max_list = []
    min_list = []
    tup = list(tup)
    for i in range(k):
        max_list.append(max(tup))
        min_list.append(min(tup))
        tup.remove(max(tup))
        tup.remove(min(tup))
    return max_list, min_list

def solve(tup, k):
    max_list = []
    min_list = []
    for i in range(k):
        max_element = max(tup)
        min_element = min(tup)
        max_list.append(max_element)
        min_list.append(min_element)
        tup = list(tup)
        tup.remove(max_element)
        tup.remove(min_element)
        tup = tuple(tup)
    return max_list, min_list
